 future, time and morality, the rationality of regret, free will and personal efficacy, and goodness and love. He shows that we can rely on our own powers of thought to arrive at a better understanding of the most fundamental parts of ourselves—and that the methods of philosophy can help get us there.Beautifully illustrated by New Yorker contributing artist Emily Bernstein, On Being Me invites us to approach life philosophically.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHuman beings. 0aPhilosophical anthropology. 0aPhilosophy. 0aSelf (Philosophy) 0aSelf (Philosophy). 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aAugustine.  aBryan Magee.  aDescartes.  aEdward Craig.  aJohn Kaag.  aMeditations.  aPhilosophy: A Very Short Introduction.  aSick Souls, Healthy Minds.  aSimon Blackburn.  aSophie’s World.  aThink.  aThomas Nagel.  aUltimate Questions.  aWhat Does It All Mean.  aa philosophical view of life.  aa reflective life.  aa well-examined life.  aa well-thought out life.  acommon human concerns.  acontemplative books.  adying.  aissues of time.  aliving a philosophical life.  aliving life philosophically.  amoral philosophy.  amorals and ethics.  apersonal identity.  aphilosophical puzzles.  aphilosophical reasoning.  aphilosophical reflections.  apower of thought.  aproblems of time.  athe meaning of life.1 aBernstein, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 